Knowledge of the pedagogical and psychological basics of acquiring and teaching of motor skills. Psychomotor abilities of schoolchildren, different teaching methods, age-related aspects of acquiring motor skills.
Survey of the dynamics of changes in the locomotory apparatus depending on age-related features and adaptation to functional activity.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of motor control and learning. During the study course, theoretical foundations of motor control and motor learning will be analyzed.And to handle the relations between functional activity and development of locomotory apparatusLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Knowledge related to theoretical basis and practical application of motor learning and motor control. Student can apply theoretical knowledge for the planning and applying motor learning process. Student is able to assess the process and stages of skill acquisition. The student understand: 1) relations between functional activity and development of locomotory apparatus; 2) the dynamics of changes in locomotory apparatus depending on age-related features and adaptation to functional activity
